benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Remove tags from bundle

covered: Valid Deletion: Scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03 and TC04 demonstrate successful deletion of tags (with and without tagDef, and with headers).
Empty Response: Tests confirm 204 responses with empty body when there are no tags to remove (TC01, TC04).
Query Parameter Handling: TagDef usage variations (TC02, TC11) and edge cases like empty array (TC16) and multiple tagDefs (TC02) are covered.
Error Handling and Input Validation: Invalid bundleId format (TC05), invalid tagDef (TC07), mixed validity (TC13), and missing required header (TC08).
Authorization: Unauthorized user case (TC09) is covered.
Server Availability and Timeouts: Service unavailable (TC10) and timeout scenarios (TC18).
Data Integrity: Integration check after deletion verifying remaining tags (TC17).
Header Handling: Deletion with X-Killbill-Reason and X-Killbill-Comment (TC03).
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit test for soft-delete semantics (e.g., a tombstoned/deleted flag behavior).
403 Forbidden Coverage: Only 401 Unauthorized tested; no test for 403 (insufficient privileges).
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 Too Many Requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses.
Internal Server Error: No test simulating 500 errors (beyond 503/504).
Observability/Audit Logging: No dedicated tests verifying audit logs or event emission for deletions.
recommendations: Add a test covering 403 Forbidden for insufficient privileges on tag deletion.
Introduce rate-limiting tests (e.g., 429 Too Many Requests) to assess throttling behavior under load.
Add tests for caching headers on DELETE responses (ETag/Cache-Control) if applicable.
Simulate 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to verify server-side error handling and messaging.
Add tests for idempotency and repeated DELETE calls to ensure consistent behavior.
Add coverage for auditing/logging of tag deletion operations to support observability.
